Pedro Sanchez, Spain's Prime Minister, is leading the charge for EU intervention into energy prices, arguing that rising gas prices are in turn causing electricity prices to soar. However, Germany and the Netherlands are arguing against intervention - stating that when prices are high, there is no silver bullet other than reducing demand or supply. Tensions are running high amid the leaders, and diplomats say Sanchez is threatening to veto the summit conclusions if EU leaders don't sway towards intervention. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES.... 